===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Sisquoc had a population of 191. The population density was {{convert|85.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Sisquoc was 133 (69.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 6 (3.1%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 3 (1.6%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 16 (8.4%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 33 (17.3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 57 persons (29.8%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Sisquoc CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0672086 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 72 households, out of which 29 (40.3%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 36 (50.0%) were married-couple households, 13 (18.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 15 (20.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 8 (11.1%) had a male householder with no partner present. 14 households (19.4%) were one person, and 3 (4.2%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.65.<ref name=DP1/> There were 52 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (72.2% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Sisquoc CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0672086 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 48 people (25.1%) under the age of 18, 7 people (3.7%) aged 18 to 24, 55 people (28.8%) aged 25 to 44, 57 people (29.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 24 people (12.6%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 38.5{{nbsp}}years. There were 94 males and 97 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 76 housing units at an average density of {{convert|34.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 72 (94.7%) were occupied. Of these, 38 (52.8%) were owner-occupied, and 34 (47.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

